result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (1st) and Operating w/ PAC >=0.15 (1st). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (1st) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC >=0.15 (1st) was dismissed by the court.

  • Donald L Wurtinger was found guilty of Hit and Run-Involve Injury, an unclassified felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.67(1).
  • Donald L Wurtinger was found guilty of OWI (1st). This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Donald L Wurtinger in court with attorney Wright C. Laufenberg.  Galen Bayne-Allison appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 15CF157 and 15TR692 @ 1:46 p.m. Agreement stated - 15CF157 - State will move to amend, under 967.055, ct 2 to simple OWI 1st, Def would plead to that and to ct 1. Ct 3 would be amended to simple PAC and dismissed and consolidated. Ct 1 - withheld sentence, 18 months probation, restitution $200.40, no possession or consumption of alcohol, no presence in taverns. Ct 2 - $970 fine and costs, 7 month revocation, AODA and follow through, 1 yr IID. (BAC .173) State gives reasons and circumstances for agreement and has complied with victim rights. Court reviews 967.055. Statement by Atty Laufenberg. Response by State. Atty Laufenberg agrees with recited agreement. Def agrees. Plea quest. reviewed w/Def. Court grants motion to amend ct 2 to straight OWI 1st. No contest plea. Plea to ct 1 - no contest. Court grants motion to amend ct 3 and dismisses.  Court gives findings for amendment. (Verified with Judge, ct 3 amended to straight PAC and dismissed) Constitutional rights, possible penalties reviewed. Atty Laufenberg satisfied. Court finds Def understands and pleas freely & voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts pleas and finds guilty of ct 1 as charged and ct 2 as amended OWI 1st with BAC .17. Sentencing remarks by State. Victim impact statements read by Atty Bayne-Allison and victim-witness coordinator. Court questions victim-witness coordinator and relative of victim. Sentencing remarks by Atty Laufenberg. Discussion regarding restitution. Nothing from Defendant. Sentencing remarks by the Court. Court asks that Def's health issues be stated for the record. Response by State. Additional remarks by the Court, will follow agreement. Ct 1 - sentence withheld, 18 months probation, court costs, DNA sample and surcharge, restitution $200.40 to victim, no use or possession of alcohol, no presence in taverns, no credit if revoked. Ct 2 - $1,020 fine and costs including IID surcharge, 7 month revocation, credit for any admin. susp. AODA and follow through, IID 1 yr effective upon application. Postconviction rights. Apply bond to ct 2, pp for balance. Def needs to report for booking.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Recalled @ 3:07 - 15TR692 - State moves to dismiss w/prejudice. Court grants.
Plea/sentencing hearing on November 2, 2016 at 01:30 pm.
